Correct Answer

Black can capture three stones by playing an atari with 1.

::dia(#ch6_3_dia14) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F8G8 ab="E7 E8 F6 F8 G5 H6 H7" aw="F7 G6 G7 G8 G9 H5 J5 J6 J8"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries with 1, White plays 2 and his stones cannot be captured.

::h2
Problem 28

::dia(#ch6_3_dia15) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13G8 ab="E9 F10 G10 G8 H6 H7 H8 H9 J9 N13" aw="G6 G9 H10 H5 J10 J6 J7 J8 K9"
Problem 28
Black to play

How should Black atari the lone white stone?

::h3
Answer 28

::dia(#ch6_3_dia16) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G8 ab="E9 F10 G10 G8 H6 H7 H8 H9 J9" aw="G6 G9 H10 H5 J10 J6 J7 J8 K9"
Correct Answer

If Black ataries with 1, the lone white stone cannot escape.

::dia(#ch6_3_dia17) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F9G8 ab="E9 F10 F9 G10 H6 H7 H8 H9 J9" aw="G6 G8 G9 H10 H5 J10 J6 J7 J8 K9"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 is the wrong direction. White will capture five black stones with 2.

::h2
Problem 29

::dia(#ch6_3_dia18) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13G9 ab="G7 G9 H8 J9 N13" aw="F7 G8 H9"
Problem 29
Black to play

How can Black make a double atari?

(__double atari__ – an atari against two separated stones at the same time)

::h3
Answer 29

::dia(#ch6_3_dia19) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G9 ab="G7 G9 H8 J9" aw="F7 G8 H9"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is a double atari. One of the two threatened white stones will be captured.

::dia(#ch6_3_dia20) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=F8G9 ab="F8 G7 H8 J9" aw="F7 G8 G9 H9"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries with 1, White will connect with 2 and his stones cannot be captured.

::h2
Problem 30

::dia(#ch6_3_dia21) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13J5 ab="G4 G5 H4 J2 J3 J5 N13" aw="F6 G6 H5 J4 K3 L4"
Problem 30
Black to play

How can Black play a double atari?

::h3
Answer 30

::dia(#ch6_3_dia22) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=J5 ab="G4 G5 H4 J2 J3 J5" aw="F6 G6 H5 J4 K3 L4"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is a double atari. One of the two threatened white stones will be captured.

::dia(#ch6_3_dia23) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=H6J5 ab="G4 G5 H4 H6 J2 J3" aw="F6 G6 H5 J4 J5 K3 L4"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries with 1, White connects with 2 and his stones cannot be captured.


::chapter(#ch6_4)

::h3
Connecting and Separating Stones

::h2
Problem 31

::dia(#ch6_4_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13D4 ab="D3 D4 D5 N13" aw="C4 E4"
Problem 31
Black to play

How should Black play?

::h3
Answer 31

::dia(#ch6_4_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=D4 ab="D3 D4 D5" aw="C4 E4"
Correct Answer

Black should connect his stones with 1. This also separates White’s two stones. Separating your opponent’s stones is an important consideration when fighting.

::dia(#ch6_4_dia2) sz=13 vw=A6H13 base=none at=1 mv=C8D9 ab="C8 D10 D8" aw="C9 D9 E9"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, it is White who separates Black into two groups and links up his own stones with 2. Black is at a disadvantage.

::h2
Problem 32

::dia(#ch6_4_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13J3 ab="H3 J3 J4 K5 L5 N13" aw="F3 G4 H4 K3 L4"
Problem 32
Black to play

How should Black play so as to link up all of his stones?

::h3
Answer 32

::dia(#ch6_4_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=J3 ab="H3 J3 J4 K5 L5" aw="F3 G4 H4 K3 L4"
Correct Answer

By playing 1, Black links up his stones into one strong group.

::dia(#ch6_4_dia5) sz=9 vw=A2J9 base=none at=1 mv=D6E4 ab="D4 D6 E5 F6 G6" aw="B4 C5 D5 E4 F4 G5"
Wrong Answer

If White is allowed to cut with 2, Black’s stone on the third line can be captured while White’s stones are all linked up.

::h2
Problem 33

::dia(#ch6_4_dia6) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13F1 ab="B2 B3 C4 D5 F1 F2 F3 F4 F5 N13" aw="C2 D3 E2 G2 H3 J4"
Problem 33
Black to play

How can Black keep the two groups of white stones separated?

::h3
Answer 33

::dia(#ch6_4_dia7) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F1 ab="B2 B3 C4 D5 F1 F2 F3 F4 F5" aw="C2 D3 E2 G2 H3 J4"
Correct Answer

When Black plays 1, White is unable to link up his stones. Playing to the left or right of 1 also prevents White from linking up.

::dia(#ch6_4_dia8) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=F6 ab="B7 B8 C9 D10 F10 F7 F8 F9" aw="C7 D8 E7 F6 G7 H8 J9"
If White Plays First

If it is White’s turn to play, he can link up his stones by playing underneath with 1.

::h2
Problem 34

::dia(#ch6_4_dia9) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13L5 ab="K3 K6 K7 L4 L5 N13" aw="J2 J3 J5 J6 K5"
Problem 34
Black to play

How should Black respond to White 1?

::h3
Answer 34

::dia(#ch6_4_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=L5 ab="K3 K6 K7 L4 L5" aw="J2 J3 J5 J6 K5"
Correct Answer

By playing 1, Black links up his upper and lower stones to make one group.

::dia(#ch6_4_dia11) sz=13 vw=A6H13 base=none at=1 mv=E7F10 ab="E11 E12 E7 E8 F9" aw="D10 D11 D7 D8 E10 F10"
Wrong Answer

If Black lets White play 2, he will not be able to link up and will end up with two weak groups.


::chapter(#ch6_5)

::h3
Ko

::h2
Problem 35

::dia(#ch6_5_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F9N13G9 ab="E9 F10 F11 F8 G7 G9 N13" aw="D9 E8 F9 G10 G8 H9"
Problem 35
Black to play

White plays a double atari with 1. How should Black answer?

::h3
Answer 35

::dia(#ch6_5_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G9 ab="E9 F10 F11 F8 G7 G9" aw="D9 E8 F9 G10 G8 H9"
Correct Answer

Taking the ko with Black 1 is the only move.

::dia(#ch6_5_dia2) sz=9 vw=A2J9 base=none at=1 mv=E5F3E6 ab="E5 F3 F4 F6 F7 G3" aw="D5 E4 E6 F5 G4 G6 H5"
Wrong Answer

If Black connects with 1, White takes a stone with 2 and Black’s stones are separated.

::h2
Problem 36

::dia(#ch6_5_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E8 ab="D8 E7 E9 F10 F8" aw="E6 E8 F7 F9 G8"
Problem 36

White 1 captures a black stone in a ko. How should Black reply?

(__ko__ – a shape in which your stone is captured, but it is illegal to retake the capturing stone, even though you can occupy all of its liberties)

::h3
Answer 36

::dia(#ch6_5_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=D7 ab="D7 D8 E7 E9 F10" aw="E6 E8 F7 F9 G8"
Correct Answer

In this case, Black should connect with 1 without capturing a stone.

::dia(#ch6_5_dia5) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F8 ab="D8 E7 E9 F10 F8" aw="E6 E8 F7 F9 G8"
An Illegal Move

Black cannot retake with 1. This is against the rules.

::h2
Problem 37

::dia(#ch6_5_dia6) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F1N13E1 ab="E1 E3 F2 F3 G1 G4 H4 J4 K4 L2 L3 N13" aw="C2 D1 D3 D5 E2 F1 G2 H3 J2"
Problem 37
Black to play

How should Black respond to White 1?

::h3
Answer 37

::dia(#ch6_5_dia7) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E1 ab="E1 E3 F2 F3 G1 G4 H4 J4 K4 L2 L3" aw="C2 D1 D3 D5 E2 F1 G2 H3 J2"
Correct Answer

Taking the ko with 1 is the correct move.

::dia(#ch6_5_dia8) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=H6E6 ab="E8 F7 F8 G6 G9 H6 H9 J9 K9 L7 L8" aw="C7 D10 D6 D8 E6 E7 F6 G7 H8 J7"
Wrong Answer

If Black extends to 1, White connects with 2 and the two black stones cannot escape.

::h2
Problem 38

::dia(#ch6_5_dia9) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13D3 ab="C3 C6 D2 D3 D4 E3 G4 N13" aw="C2 E2 E4 E5 F3"
Problem 38
Black to play

What is Black’s best move?

::h3
Answer 38

::dia(#ch6_5_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=D3 ab="C3 C6 D2 D3 D4 E3 G4" aw="C2 E2 E4 E5 F3"
Correct Answer

Black should connect with 1 so that White cannot start a ko fight.

::dia(#ch6_5_dia11) sz=13 vw=A6H13 base=none at=1 mv=E8F7D8 ab="C11 C8 D7 D9 E8 F7 G9" aw="C7 D8 E10 E7 E9 F8"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White starts a ko with 2. Black is at a disadvantage.


::chapter(#ch6_6)

::h3
Ladders

::h2
Problem 39

::dia(#ch6_6_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13F2N13E3D3E2D2E1F1 ab="D2 D3 E4 F1 F2 F5 G3 G6 H4 H6 J5 N13" aw="E1 E2 E3 F3 F4 G4 G5 H5 H7 J6 K6 N13"
Problem 39
Black to play

How can Black capture the five white stones?

::h3
Answer 39

::dia(#ch6_6_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F2E3D3E2D2E1F1 ab="D2 D3 E4 F1 F2 F5 G3 G6 H4 H6 J5" aw="E1 E2 E3 F3 F4 G4 G5 H5 H7 J6 K6"
Correct Answer

If Black ataries with 1 to 5, White cannot escape. This kind of situation is called a ladder.

::dia(#ch6_6_dia2) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=E8F7 ab="E8 E9 F10 G11 G8 H11 H9 J10" aw="F7 F8 F9 G10 G9 H10 H12 J11 K11"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries with 1, White is able to escape by extending to 2.

::h2
Problem 40

::dia(#ch6_6_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=D9E9E8F8F7G7G6H6H5J5N13J4 ab="C10 C11 D11 D9 E8 E9 F10 F7 F8 G6 G7 H5 H6 J5" aw="C9 D10 D8 E10 E7 F6 F9 G5 G8 H4 H7 J4 J6 K5 N13"
Problem 40
White to play

Black plays double atari with 1. How should White respond?

::h3
Answer 40

::dia(#ch6_6_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=J4 ab="C10 C11 D11 D9 E8 E9 F10 F7 F8 G6 G7 H5 H6 J5" aw="C9 D10 D8 E10 E7 F6 F9 G5 G8 H4 H7 J4 J6 K5"
Correct Answer

If White takes ten stones with 1, Black no longer has a double atari on the white stones.

::dia(#ch6_6_dia5) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F9E11G9 ab="C10 C11 D11 D9 E8 E9 F10 F7 F8 G6 G7 G9 H5 H6 J5" aw="C9 D10 D8 E10 E11 E7 F6 F9 G5 G8 H4 H7 J6 K5"
Wrong Answer

If White runs away with 1 to save his two stones, Black captures with 2 and the ten black stones are no longer in atari.


::chapter(#ch6_7)

::h3
Living Groups and Dead Groups

::h2
Problem 41

::dia(#ch6_7_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13E13 ab="E12 E13 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13 N13" aw="D11 D12 E11 F11 G11 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13"
Problem 41
Black to play

How can Black live with his seven stones?

(A group of stones is said to be alive if it can make two ‘eyes’. Such stones can never be captured. A group of stones is said to be dead if it cannot make two eyes. Such stones will be taken off the board as prisoners at the end of the game.)

::h3
Answer 41

::dia(#ch6_7_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E13 ab="E12 E13 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13" aw="D11 D12 E11 F11 G11 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13"
Correct Answer

Black can make life for his group by playing at 1.

::dia(#ch6_7_dia2) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=E13 ab="E12 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13" aw="D11 D12 E11 E13 F11 G11 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13"
If White Plays First

If it is White’s turn, White 1 will kill the black group.

::h2
Problem 42

::dia(#ch6_7_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13G12 ab="D11 D12 D13 E10 F10 G10 G11 G12 H10 J11 K11 K12 K13 N13" aw="E12 E13 F11 F12 G13 H12 J12 J13"
Problem 42
Black to play

Where should Black play to kill the white stones?

::h3
Answer 42

::dia(#ch6_7_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G12 ab="D11 D12 D13 E10 F10 G10 G11 G12 H10 J11 K11 K12 K13" aw="E12 E13 F11 F12 G13 H12 J12 J13"
Correct Answer

Black 1 kills the white stones. Eventually, Black will be able to take these stones off the board.

::dia(#ch6_7_dia5) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=G12 ab="D11 D12 D13 E10 F10 G10 G11 H10 J11 K11 K12 K13" aw="E12 E13 F11 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13"
If White Plays First

If it’s White’s turn to play, he can live by playing 1.

::h2
Problem 43

::dia(#ch6_7_dia6) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13H10 ab="G10 G11 G12 G13 H10 H12 J11 J12 J13 N13" aw="F10 F11 F12 F13 G9 H9 J9 K10 K11 K12 K13"
Problem 43
Black to play

How can Black play so as to give his eight stones a living shape?

::h3
Answer 43

::dia(#ch6_7_dia7) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=H10 ab="G10 G11 G12 G13 H10 H12 J11 J12 J13" aw="F10 F11 F12 F13 G9 H9 J9 K10 K11 K12 K13"
Correct Answer

Black can make life for his group by playing 1.

::dia(#ch6_7_dia8) sz=9 vw=A2J9 base=none at=1 mv=E6D6 ab="C6 C7 C8 C9 D8 E6 E7 E8 E9" aw="B6 B7 B8 B9 C5 D5 D6 E5 F6 F7 F8 F9"
Wrong Answer

If White gets to play 2, the black stones will die.

::h2
Problem 44

::dia(#ch6_7_dia9) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13G6 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F10 F6 G10 G5 G6 H10 H5 J5 J8 J9 K6 K7 N13" aw="F7 F8 G7 G9 H6 H8 H9 J6 J7"
Problem 44
Black to play

How can Black kill all of the white stones?

::h3
Answer 44

::dia(#ch6_7_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G6 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F10 F6 G10 G5 G6 H10 H5 J5 J8 J9 K6 K7" aw="F7 F8 G7 G9 H6 H8 H9 J6 J7"
Correct Answer

Black 1 kills all of the white stones.

::dia(#ch6_7_dia11) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F9G6 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F10 F6 F9 G10 G5 H10 H5 J5 J8 J9 K6 K7" aw="F7 F8 G6 G7 G9 H6 H8 H9 J6 J7"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays any other move, White can live by making two eyes with 2.

::h2
Problem 45

::dia(#ch6_7_dia12) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13A1G13 ab="A4 B4 C4 D1 D11 D12 D13 D2 D3 E11 F11 G11 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13" aw="A1 A3 B2 B3 C1 C2 E12 E13 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13 N13"
Problem 45
White to play

How can White live with his stones at the top and at the bottom?

::h3
Answer 45

::dia(#ch6_7_dia13) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="A4 B4 C4 D1 D11 D12 D13 D2 D3 E11 F11 G11 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13" aw="A1 A3 B2 B3 C1 C2 E12 E13 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13"
Correct Answer

White can make life in both positions by playing at 1.

::dia(#ch6_7_dia14) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="A1 A4 B4 C4 D1 D11 D12 D13 D2 D3 E11 F11 G11 G13 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13" aw="A3 B2 B3 C1 C2 E12 E13 F12 G12 H12 J12 J13"
If Black Plays First

Black 1 will kill both white groups.

::h2
Problem 46

::dia(#ch6_7_dia15) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F4 F5 F9 G10 G4 H10 H4 J5 J6 J7 J8 J9" aw="F6 F7 F8 G5 G6 G9 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9"
Problem 46
Black to play

What about the white group in the center? Is it alive or dead?

::h3
Answer 46

::dia(#ch6_7_dia16) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F4 F5 F9 G10 G4 H10 H4 J5 J6 J7 J8 J9" aw="F6 F7 F8 G5 G6 G9 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9"
Correct Answer

White is dead.

::dia(#ch6_7_dia17) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F4 F5 F9 G10 G4 H10 H4 J5 J6 J7 J8 J9" aw="F6 F7 F8 G5 G7 G9 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9"
For Reference

If this were the position, White would be alive because he has two eyes.


::chapter(#ch6_8)

::h3
How to Play in the Opening

::h2
Problem 47

::dia(#ch6_8_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13D4D3C4C3E4E3D5C5 ab="L11 L4" aw="C3 C4 C5 D11 D3 D4 D5 E3 E4 N13"
Problem 47
White to play

Where does White want to play?

(There is more than one correct answer.)

::h3
Answer 47

::dia(#ch6_8_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="L11 L4" aw="D11"
Correct Answer

You can gain the most advantage by playing in an empty corner. Any of the moves from A to D is correct.

::dia(#ch6_8_dia2) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="L11 L4" aw="D11"
Correct Answer

Any one of the four moves shown in this diagram is also good.

::h2
Problem 48

::dia(#ch6_8_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13L4L3K4K3J4J3L5K5 ab="D4 J3 J4 K10 K3 K4 K5 L3 L4 L5 N13" aw="D11 D9"
Problem 48
Black to play

Where should Black play?

(There is more than one correct answer.)

::h3
Answer 48

::dia(#ch6_8_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="D4 K10" aw="D11 D9"
Correct Answer

Black should play in the empty corner on one of the points from A to H. Any one of these moves would be correct.

::dia(#ch6_8_dia5) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=H11L3 ab="D4 H11 K10" aw="D11 D9 L3"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays at 1, White will take the empty corner with 2 and Black will be at a slight disadvantage.

::h2
Problem 49

::dia(#ch6_8_dia6) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13C4D3 ab="D4 K10 K4" aw="C3 C4 D11 D3 N13"
Problem 49
White to play

How does White answer Black 1?

::h3
Answer 49

::dia(#ch6_8_dia7) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=C4 ab="D4 K10 K4" aw="C3 C4 D11"
Correct Answer

Either White 1 or White A would be a good move.

::dia(#ch6_8_dia8) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=D9D3 ab="D3 D4 K10 K4" aw="C3 D11 D9"
Wrong Answer

If White plays at 1 or in another corner, Black 2 puts White at a disadvantage.

::h2
Problem 50

::dia(#ch6_8_dia9) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13J11J9K9K11 ab="J11 J3 J9 K10 K11 K9 L4 N13" aw="D11 D4 J10"
Problem 50
Black to play

White 1 is a bad move, but how should Black respond?

::h3
Answer 50

::dia(#ch6_8_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=J11 ab="J11 J3 K10 L4" aw="D11 D4 J10"
Correct Answer

Black 1 or any of the moves from A to C would be correct.

::dia(#ch6_8_dia11) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=C9K9 ab="C9 J3 K10 L4" aw="D11 D4 J10 K9"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1 or on a point other than in the upper right corner, White 2 would put Black at a disadvantage.


::chapter(#ch6_9)

::h3
Endgame and Other Moves

::h2
Problem 51

::dia(#ch6_9_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G9N13F9E9 ab="E9 F9 G10 G8 H7 H9 N13" aw="D9 E10 E8 F10 F8 G7 G9"
Problem 51
Black to play

How should Black play after White captures two stones with 1?

::h3
Answer 51

::dia(#ch6_9_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F9 ab="F9 G10 G8 H7 H9" aw="D9 E10 E8 F10 F8 G7 G9"
Correct Answer

Black should immediately capture one white stone with 1.

::dia(#ch6_9_dia2) sz=13 vw=A5N13 base=none at=1 mv=H8 ab="G10 G8 H7 H8 H9" aw="D9 E10 E8 F10 F8 G7 G9"
Wrong Answer

Neglecting to capture the white stone and connecting with 1 will put Black at a disadvantage.

::h2
Problem 52

::dia(#ch6_9_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F10G10E9F9N13G9 ab="D9 E10 E8 F11 F8 G11 G9 H10 N13" aw="E9 F10 F9 G10 G7 G8 H9 J10"
Problem 52
Black to play

How should Black play after White captures a stone with 1?

::h3
Answer 52

::dia(#ch6_9_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G9 ab="D9 E10 E8 F11 F8 G11 G9 H10" aw="E9 F10 F9 G10 G7 G8 H9 J10"
Correct Answer

Black should play at 1 and capture four stones.

::dia(#ch6_9_dia5) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=H11G9 ab="D9 E10 E8 F11 F8 G11 H10 H11" aw="E9 F10 F9 G10 G7 G8 G9 H9 J10"
Wrong Answer

If Black connects with 1, White will save his four stones by playing 2.

::h2
Problem 53

::dia(#ch6_9_dia6) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="B2 C3 D1 D3 E3 F10 F2 F3 G1 G11 G9 H11 H9 J11 J9 K11 K9 L10" aw="C1 C2 D2 E1 E10 E2 F1 F11 F9 G10 G2 G3 G4 H10 J10"
Problem 53
Black to play

Can Black play 1 at the top and at the bottom?

::h3
Answer 53

::dia(#ch6_9_dia7) sz=13 vw=A7N13 base=none at=1 ab="F10 G11 G9 H11 H9 J11 J9 K11 K9 L10" aw="E10 F11 F9 G10 H10 J10"
An Illegal Move

Black 1 is an illegal move. If the point A were occupied by either Black or White, then Black 1 would be possible.

::dia(#ch6_9_dia8) sz=13 vw=A7N13 base=none at=1 ab="B8 C9 D7 D9 E9 F8 F9 G7" aw="C7 C8 D8 E7 E8 F7 G10 G8 G9 J8"
An Illegal Move

Black 1 here is also an illegal move. However, if Black occupied the point A, then Black could play at 1 and capture six stones.

::h2
Problem 54

::dia(#ch6_9_dia9) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="F2 F3 G1 G3 H1 H3 J3 K2" aw="E2 E3 F1 G2 H2 J1 J2"
Problem 54
Black to play

How about here? Can Black play at 1?

::h3
Answer 54

::dia(#ch6_9_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="F2 F3 G1 G3 H1 H3 J3 K2" aw="E2 E3 F1 G2 H2 J1 J2"
An Illegal Move

Black 1 cannot be played. If Black occupied the point A, Black 1 would capture four stones.

::dia(#ch6_9_dia11) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=G6 ab="F7 F8 G6 G8 H8 J8 K7" aw="E7 E8 F6 G7 H7 J6 J7"
For Reference

In this position, Black 1 is a legal move.

::h2
Problem 55

::dia(#ch6_9_dia12) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="F1 F10 F2 F9 G10 G2 G8 H10 H2 H7 J1 J2 J8 J9" aw="G9 H1 H9"
Problem 55
Black to play

In the positions at the top and bottom, can Black remove the white stones from the board after he plays at 1?

::h3
Answer 55

::dia(#ch6_9_dia13) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="F1 F10 F2 F9 G10 G2 G8 H10 H2 H7 J1 J2 J8 J9" aw="G9 H1 H9"
Correct Answer

The white stones cannot be taken off the board. If A were occupied by either Black or White, then Black 1 would capture White’s two stones.

::dia(#ch6_9_dia14) sz=9 vw=A2J9 base=none at=1 ab="B2 B3 C3 C9 D3 D8 E2 E3 E9" aw="D2"
Correct Answer

The white stone cannot be taken. As before, if A were occupied, Black 1 would capture the white stone.

::h2
Problem 56

::dia(#ch6_9_dia15) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13J10N13E1 ab="C11 C12 C13 D12 D9 E10 E11 E12 E13 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F11 F2 F3 F4 F7 F8 G10 G5 G6 G9 J10 J4 J7 J9 K10 K12 K2 K3 K4 K5 K6 K7 K8 K9 L1 L10 L11 L12 L13 L2 N13" aw="B10 B11 B12 B13 C10 C4 C9 D1 D10 D11 D2 D3 D4 D5 D6 D7 D8 E1 E2 F12 F13 G1 G11 G2 G3 G4 G7 G8 H10 H12 H4 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9 J1 J11 J12 J13 J2 J3 J5 J6 J8 K1 K11 K13 N13"
Problem 56
Black to play

The game is over, but there are still neutral points left. Where are they?

(__neutral points__ – points which profit neither Black nor White)

::h3
Answer 56

::dia(#ch6_9_dia16) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=J10E1 ab="C11 C12 C13 D12 D9 E10 E11 E12 E13 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F11 F2 F3 F4 F7 F8 G10 G5 G6 G9 J10 J4 J7 J9 K10 K12 K2 K3 K4 K5 K6 K7 K8 K9 L1 L10 L11 L12 L13 L2" aw="B10 B11 B12 B13 C10 C4 C9 D1 D10 D11 D2 D3 D4 D5 D6 D7 D8 E1 E2 F12 F13 G1 G11 G2 G3 G4 G7 G8 H10 H12 H4 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9 J1 J11 J12 J13 J2 J3 J5 J6 J8 K1 K11 K13"
Correct Answer

There are two neutral points: Black 1 and White 2.

::dia(#ch6_9_dia17) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E1J10 ab="C11 C12 C13 D12 D9 E1 E10 E11 E12 E13 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F11 F2 F3 F4 F7 F8 G10 G5 G6 G9 J4 J7 J9 K10 K12 K2 K3 K4 K5 K6 K7 K8 K9 L1 L10 L11 L12 L13 L2" aw="B10 B11 B12 B13 C10 C4 C9 D1 D10 D11 D2 D3 D4 D5 D6 D7 D8 E2 F12 F13 G1 G11 G2 G3 G4 G7 G8 H10 H12 H4 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9 J1 J10 J11 J12 J13 J2 J3 J5 J6 J8 K1 K11 K13"
Correct Answer

If Black played 1 at the bottom and White played 2 at the top, it would have no effect on the score.

::h2
Problem 57

::dia(#ch6_9_dia18) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="C11 C12 C13 D12 D9 E1 E10 E11 E12 E13 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F11 F2 F3 F4 F7 F8 G10 G5 G6 G9 J4 J7 J9 K10 K12 K2 K3 K4 K5 K6 K7 K8 K9 L1 L10 L11 L12 L13 L2" aw="B10 B11 B12 B13 C10 C4 C9 D1 D10 D11 D2 D3 D4 D5 D6 D7 D8 E2 F12 F13 G1 G11 G2 G3 G4 G7 G8 H10 H12 H4 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9 J1 J10 J11 J12 J13 J2 J3 J5 J6 J8 K1 K11 K13"
Problem 57
Black to play

No stones have been captured. Who wins and by how many points?

::h3
Answer 57

::dia(#ch6_9_dia19) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="C11 C12 C13 D12 D9 E1 E10 E11 E12 E13 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F11 F2 F3 F4 F7 F8 G10 G5 G6 G9 J4 J7 J9 K10 K12 K2 K3 K4 K5 K6 K7 K8 K9 L1 L10 L11 L12 L13 L2" aw="B10 B11 B12 B13 C10 C4 C9 D1 D10 D11 D2 D3 D4 D5 D6 D7 D8 E2 F12 F13 G1 G11 G2 G3 G4 G7 G8 H10 H12 H4 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9 J1 J10 J11 J12 J13 J2 J3 J5 J6 J8 K1 K11 K13"
Correct Answer

Black’s territory amounts to 38 points: 33 points on the right and 5 points in the middle.

::dia(#ch6_9_dia20) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 ab="C11 C12 C13 D12 D9 E1 E10 E11 E12 E13 E3 E4 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F11 F2 F3 F4 F7 F8 G10 G5 G6 G9 J4 J7 J9 K10 K12 K2 K3 K4 K5 K6 K7 K8 K9 L1 L10 L11 L12 L13 L2" aw="B10 B11 B12 B13 C10 C4 C9 D1 D10 D11 D2 D3 D4 D5 D6 D7 D8 E2 F12 F13 G1 G11 G2 G3 G4 G7 G8 H10 H12 H4 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9 J1 J10 J11 J12 J13 J2 J3 J5 J6 J8 K1 K11 K13"
Correct Answer

White’s territory comes to 36 points: 29 points on the left and 7 points in the middle. Therefore, Black wins by 2 points.

::h2
Problem 58

::dia(#ch6_9_dia21) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13L12N13B13 ab="C11 C12 D12 D9 E1 E10 E11 E12 E13 E3 E5 E6 E7 E8 E9 F1 F11 F2 F3 F4 F7 F8 G10 G3 G4 G5 G6 G9 J5 J9 K10 K12 K13 K2 K3 K4 K5 K6 K9 L1 L10 L11 L12 L7 L8 M2 N13" aw="B11 B12 B13 C10 C13 C4 C9 D1 D10 D11 D2 D3 D4 D5 D6 D7 D8 E2 E4 F12 F13 G1 G11 G2 G7 G8 H10 H12 H13 H3 H4 H5 H6 H7 H9 J1 J10 J11 J12 J2 J3 J4 J6 J8 K1 K11 K7 K8 N13"
Problem 58
