::chapter(#ch8_4)

::h3
Seki

::h2
Problem 171

::dia(#ch8_4_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13G10 ab="E10 E11 E12 E13 F9 G10 G9 H10 H11 H12 H13 N13" aw="D10 D11 D12 D13 D9 E9 F10 F11 G11 G12 G13"
Problem 171
Black to play

How can Black get a seki?

(__seki__ – an impasse or stalemate position between groups: if one side tries to attack the other side’s group his own group dies)

::h3
Answer 171

::dia(#ch8_4_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G10 ab="E10 E11 E12 E13 F9 G10 G9 H10 H11 H12 H13" aw="D10 D11 D12 D13 D9 E9 F10 F11 G11 G12 G13"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the only move. The four black stones and the five white stones live in a seki.

::dia(#ch8_4_dia2) sz=9 vw=A2J9 base=none at=1 mv=F8 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F5 F8 G5 H6 H7 H8 H9" aw="D5 D6 D7 D8 D9 E5 F6 F7 G7 G8 G9"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 puts his own five stones in atari. White can capture five black stones on the next move. Black has failed.

::h2
Problem 172

::dia(#ch8_4_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13G7 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F5 F9 G5 G7 G9 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9 N13" aw="D6 D7 D8 D9 E10 E4 E5 F10 F4 F6 F7 F8 G10 G4 H10 H4 J5 J6 J7 J8 J9"
Problem 172
Black to play

How does Black play so that his stones live in a seki?

::h3
Answer 172

::dia(#ch8_4_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G7 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F5 F9 G5 G7 G9 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9" aw="D6 D7 D8 D9 E10 E4 E5 F10 F4 F6 F7 F8 G10 G4 H10 H4 J5 J6 J7 J8 J9"
Correct Answer

Black 1 makes a seki. If White moves to break the seki by sacrificing four stones, Black will take those stones and his group can easily make two eyes.

::dia(#ch8_4_dia5) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F8F7F6G6G7G8 ab="E6 E7 E8 E9 F5 F9 G5 G6 G8 G9 H5 H6 H7 H8 H9" aw="D6 D7 D8 D9 E10 E4 E5 F10 F4 F6 F7 F8 G10 G4 G7 H10 H4 J5 J6 J7 J8 J9"
Wrong Answer
4 played to the left of 2

If Black plays 1, White sacrifices four stones and, after Black captures with 3, destroys Black’s eye shape with 4.

::h2
Problem 173

::dia(#ch8_4_dia6) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13E13 ab="C12 C13 D11 D12 E12 E13 F11 G11 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13 N13" aw="B12 B13 C10 C11 D10 E10 E11 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13"
Problem 173
Black to play

How does Black play so that his stones live in a seki?

::h3
Answer 173

::dia(#ch8_4_dia7) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E13 ab="C12 C13 D11 D12 E12 E13 F11 G11 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13" aw="B12 B13 C10 C11 D10 E10 E11 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the only move. Both sides have one eye and share a common neutral point, so the position is a seki.

::dia(#ch8_4_dia8) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=F13E13 ab="C12 C13 D11 D12 E12 F11 F13 G11 H11 J11 K11 K12 K13" aw="B12 B13 C10 C11 D10 E10 E11 E13 F12 G12 G13 H12 J12 J13"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White captures a stone and puts five black stones into atari.

::h2
Problem 174

::dia(#ch8_4_dia9) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13H1 ab="E1 E2 E3 E4 E5 F6 F7 G2 G3 G4 G7 H7 J1 J2 J3 J4 J5 J6" aw="F1 F2 F3 F4 F5 G6 H1 H2 H3 H4 H5 H6 N13"
Problem 174
White to play

How does White play so that his stones live in a seki?

::h3
Answer 174

::dia(#ch8_4_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=H1 ab="E1 E2 E3 E4 E5 F6 F7 G2 G3 G4 G7 H7 J1 J2 J3 J4 J5 J6" aw="F1 F2 F3 F4 F5 G6 H1 H2 H3 H4 H5 H6"
Correct Answer

White 1 is the only move. White has no way to capture the three black stones, so he must settle for a seki.

::dia(#ch8_4_dia11) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=G6 ab="E10 E6 E7 E8 E9 F11 F12 G12 G7 G8 G9 H12 J10 J11 J6 J7 J8 J9" aw="F10 F6 F7 F8 F9 G11 G6 H10 H11 H7 H8 H9"
Wrong Answer

If White tries to capture the three black stones with 1, he will not be able to make two eyes and his group will eventually be captured.


