::h3
Ko

::h2
Problem 175

::dia(#ch8_5_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E13N13F13 ab="D12 D13 E12 F11 F13 G11 H11 H12 N13" aw="C11 C12 D11 E10 E11 E13 F12 G12 G13"
Problem 175
Black to play

After White 1, how can Black get a ko?

::h3
Answer 175

::dia(#ch8_5_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F13 ab="D12 D13 E12 F11 F13 G11 H11 H12" aw="C11 C12 D11 E10 E11 E13 F12 G12 G13"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the only way for Black to get a ko. Whether the black or white stones on the upper edge can be taken or not will depend on the number of ko threats each side has.

::dia(#ch8_5_dia2) sz=9 vw=A2J9 base=none at=1 mv=D9D8E8H9C9 ab="D8 D9 E8 F7 G7 H7 H8 H9" aw="C7 C8 C9 D7 E6 E7 E9 F8 G8 G9"
