::h3
Answer 177

::dia(#ch8_5_dia7) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=D8E9E8 ab="D8 E6 E7 E9 F10 F6 F8 G10 G7 G8 G9 H9 J10" aw="C8 D6 D7 D9 E10 E5 E8 F11 F5 G11 G6 H10 H11 H6 H7 H8 J9"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the only move. White 2 starts a ko, and the life or death of the Black group will depend on the outcome of this ko.

::dia(#ch8_5_dia8) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=E8E9 ab="D8 E6 E7 E8 F10 F6 F8 G10 G7 G8 G9 H9 J10" aw="C8 D6 D7 D9 E10 E5 E9 F11 F5 G11 G6 H10 H11 H6 H7 H8 J9"
Wrong Answer

If Black connects with 1, White will play 2, leaving Black will only one eye. Black is now unconditionally dead.

::h2
Problem 178

::dia(#ch8_5_dia9) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F2N13E1N13E2 ab="B1 B2 C3 C4 C5 C7 D6 E2 F1 F3 F6 G2 G3 G4 G5 N13" aw="C1 C2 D2 D3 D4 D5 E1 E3 E5 F2 F4 F5 N13"
Problem 178
White to play

How can White get a ko?

::h3
Answer 178

::dia(#ch8_5_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F2E1E2 ab="B1 B2 C3 C4 C5 C7 D6 E2 F1 F3 F6 G2 G3 G4 G5" aw="C1 C2 D2 D3 D4 D5 E1 E3 E5 F2 F4 F5"
Correct Answer

White 1 is the only move that starts a ko. Black starts a ko with 2 and the life of the white group depends on the outcome of this ko.

::dia(#ch8_5_dia11) sz=13 vw=A6H13 base=none at=1 mv=E7E6 ab="B6 B7 C10 C12 C8 C9 D11 E6 F11 F6 F8 G10 G7 G8 G9" aw="C6 C7 D10 D7 D8 D9 E10 E7 E8 F10 F7 F9"
Wrong Answer

If White connects with 1, Black will play 2, leaving White with only one eye. White is now unconditionally dead.


::chapter(#ch8_6)

::h3
Capturing Races

::h2
Problem 179

::dia(#ch8_6_dia0) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13G12 ab="D11 F10 G10 G12 H10 H12 J11 J12 N13" aw="G11 H11 J10 J13 J9 K11 K12"
Problem 179
Black to play

How can Black capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 179

::dia(#ch8_6_dia1) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=G12 ab="D11 F10 G10 G12 H10 H12 J11 J12" aw="G11 H11 J10 J13 J9 K11 K12"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the only move. After this move, the two white stones can’t avoid capture.

::dia(#ch8_6_dia2) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=F11G12 ab="D11 F10 F11 G10 H10 H12 J11 J12" aw="G11 G12 H11 J10 J13 J9 K11 K12"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries from the left with 1, White 2 will capture three black stones.

::h2
Problem 180

::dia(#ch8_6_dia3) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13F12 ab="D11 D12 E10 E9 F11 F12 G11 H11 N13" aw="E11 E12 F10 G10 H10 H12 J11"
Problem 180
Black to play

How can Black capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 180

::dia(#ch8_6_dia4) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=F12 ab="D11 D12 E10 E9 F11 F12 G11 H11" aw="E11 E12 F10 G10 H10 H12 J11"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the vital point. This move will capture two white stones.

::dia(#ch8_6_dia5) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=E13F12 ab="D11 D12 E10 E13 E9 F11 G11 H11" aw="E11 E12 F10 F12 G10 H10 H12 J11"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries on the edge with 1, White 2 will capture three black stones.

::h2
Problem 181

::dia(#ch8_6_dia6) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13J13N13J12L12 ab="E11 E12 F10 F9 G9 H10 H11 H12 H13 J11 J12 K12 N13" aw="F12 G10 G11 G12 G13 H9 J10 J13 J9 K11 L11 L12 N13"
Problem 181
White to play

How can White capture five black stones?

::h3
Answer 181

::dia(#ch8_6_dia7) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=J13J12L12 ab="E11 E12 F10 F9 G9 H10 H11 H12 H13 J11 J12 K12" aw="F12 G10 G11 G12 G13 H9 J10 J13 J9 K11 L11 L12"
Correct Answer

White 1, followed by White 3, is the correct answer. White will capture seven stones.

::dia(#ch8_6_dia8) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=L12F11 ab="E11 E12 F10 F11 F9 G9 H10 H11 H12 H13 J11 K12" aw="F12 G10 G11 G12 G13 H9 J10 J9 K11 L11 L12"
Wrong Answer

If White plays 1, Black will atari with 2 and capture five white stones on the next move.

::h2
