Problem 182
White to play

How can White capture seven black stones?

::h3
Answer 182

::dia(#ch8_6_dia10) sz=13 vw=A1N13 base=none at=1 mv=H4H2J4G2 ab="D2 D5 E2 E5 F3 F4 G3 G4 G5 H3 H5 J4" aw="E3 E4 F2 F5 F6 G2 G6 H2 H4 H6 J3 J5"
Correct Answer

White 1, followed by White 3, is the correct answer. White will capture seven stones on the next move.

::dia(#ch8_6_dia11) sz=13 vw=A6N13 base=none at=1 mv=J9D9 ab="D10 D7 D9 E10 E7 F8 F9 G10 G8 G9 H10 H8" aw="E8 E9 F10 F11 F7 G11 H11 H9 J10 J8 J9"
Wrong Answer

If White connects with 1, Black will play 2 and capture two white stones on the next move.


::chapter(#ch9)

::h2
Introductory Problems Level Four


::chapter(#ch9_1)

::h3
Atari

::h2
Problem 183

::dia(#ch9_1_dia0) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=F5G5K10E5 ab="D2 E1 E3 E5 F2 F4 F6 G3 G4 G6 H5 K10" aw="D3 D4 D5 E4 E6 F1 F5 G2 G5 H3 H4"
Problem 183
Black to play

How should Black play?

::h3
Answer 183

::dia(#ch9_1_dia1) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=E7 ab="D4 E3 E5 E7 F4 F6 F8 G5 G6 G8 H7" aw="D5 D6 D7 E6 E8 F3 F7 G4 G7 H5 H6"
Correct Answer

Black should capture two stones with 1. Even if White recaptures, Black is no longer in atari.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia2) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=F6G6E5G5F4F5E4 ab="D4 E3 E5 F4 F5 F6 F8 G5 G6 G8 H7" aw="D5 D6 D7 E4 E6 E8 F3 F7 G4 G7 H5 H6"
Wrong Answer

If Black connects with 1, his stones are still in atari and White 2 will capture six black stones. This is a disaster for Black.

::h2
Problem 184

::dia(#ch9_1_dia3) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=C2K10B2 ab="B2 C1 C3 D1 D2 E2 K10" aw="C2 D1 D3 E1 E3 F1 F2"
Problem 184
Black to play

Which stone should Black capture?

::h3
Answer 184

::dia(#ch9_1_dia4) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=B4 ab="B4 C3 C5 D2 D4 E4" aw="C4 D3 D5 E2 E5 F3 F4"
Correct Answer

Black should capture the stone on the outside with Black 1.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia5) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=E3 ab="C3 C5 D2 D4 E3 E4" aw="C4 D3 D5 E2 E5 F3 F4"
Wrong Answer

If Black captures a stone with 1 here, a snapback arises and White will play to the left of 1, capturing three black stones.

::h2
Problem 185

::dia(#ch9_1_dia6) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19G18 ab="D18 E18 F17 G18 J17 M19" aw="C18 D17 E17 F18"
Problem 185
Black to play

From which direction should Black atari?

::h3
Answer 185

::dia(#ch9_1_dia7) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=G18 ab="D18 E18 F17 G18 J17" aw="C18 D17 E17 F18"
Correct Answer

If Black ataries with 1, the isolated white stone on the second line cannot escape.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia8) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=F19G18 ab="D18 E18 F17 F19 J17" aw="C18 D17 E17 F18 G18"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries from below with 1, White’s stone can no longer be captured after he extends to 2. Now it is the three black stones on the left that will be captured.

::h2
Problem 186

::dia(#ch9_1_dia9) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19J13 ab="D14 E12 E13 E15 F16 G12 G15 H14 J13 M19" aw="E14 F12 F13 F14 F15 G13 G14 H13 J15 K13"
Problem 186
Black to play

How can Black capture eight white stones?

::h3
Answer 186

::dia(#ch9_1_dia10) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 mv=J13 ab="D14 E12 E13 E15 F16 G12 G15 H14 J13" aw="E14 F12 F13 F14 F15 G13 G14 H13 J15 K13"
Correct Answer

After Black ataries with 1, the eight white stones cannot escape.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia11) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 mv=J14J13 ab="D14 E12 E13 E15 F16 G12 G15 H14 J14" aw="E14 F12 F13 F14 F15 G13 G14 H13 J13 J15 K13"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 here fails. When White connects with 2, he can no longer be captured.

::h2
Problem 187

::dia(#ch9_1_dia12) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10H7 ab="D5 F7 G5 G6 H7 K10" aw="F8 G7 H5 H6"
Problem 187
Black to play

White 1 is a bad move. How should Black reply?

::h3
Answer 187

::dia(#ch9_1_dia13) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=H9 ab="D7 F9 G7 G8 H9" aw="F10 G9 H7 H8"
Correct Answer

Black should play 1. The white stone in atari cannot escape.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia14) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=F10E10H9G10 ab="D7 E10 F9 G10 G7 G8" aw="F10 G9 H7 H8 H9"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries with 1, White can connect with 2. Even though Black has captured a white stone, his result is inferior to the correct answer.

::h2
Problem 188

::dia(#ch9_1_dia15) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=D2K10F2K10D1 ab="D2 E3 E4 F2 G4 K10" aw="C2 C3 D1 D3 E2 K10"
Problem 188
Black to play

How should Black answer White 1?

::h3
Answer 188

::dia(#ch9_1_dia16) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=D4F4D3 ab="D4 E5 E6 F4 G6" aw="C4 C5 D3 D5 E4"
Correct Answer

Even though he loses a stone, Black 1 is the right move.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia17) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=D3F4 ab="D3 D4 E5 E6 G6" aw="C4 C5 D5 E4 F4"
Wrong Answer

If Black tries to escape with 1, White extends to 2 and Black’s two stones on the edge cannot escape. This is a big loss for Black.

::h2
Problem 189

::dia(#ch9_1_dia18) sz=19 vw=A9L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19G16 ab="C15 C16 D17 E14 E15 E17 F13 F17 G12 G15 G16 H11 H14 J12 J13 L19" aw="C14 D13 D15 E16 F14 F15 F16 G13 G14 H12 H13"
Problem 189
Black to play

How should Black atari the eight white stones?

::h3
Answer 189

::dia(#ch9_1_dia19) sz=19 vw=A9L19 base=none at=1 mv=G16 ab="C15 C16 D17 E14 E15 E17 F13 F17 G12 G15 G16 H11 H14 J12 J13" aw="C14 D13 D15 E16 F14 F15 F16 G13 G14 H12 H13"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, no matter how White replies, his eight stones cannot avoid being captured.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia20) sz=19 vw=A9L19 base=none at=1 mv=D16G16 ab="C15 C16 D16 D17 E14 E15 E17 F13 F17 G12 G15 H11 H14 J12 J13" aw="C14 D13 D15 E16 F14 F15 F16 G13 G14 G16 H12 H13"
