If Black plays 1, White can escape with his eight stones with 2.

::h2
Problem 190

::dia(#ch9_1_dia21) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10F3K10G2H3 ab="C1 D1 D2 E1 E3 F1 F3 G1 H1 H3 J2 K10" aw="D1 E1 E2 F1 F2 F4 G1 G2 H2 H4 K10"
Problem 190
Black to play

How should Black play?

::h3
Answer 190

::dia(#ch9_1_dia22) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=F5G4H5 ab="C3 D2 D4 E1 E5 F2 F5 G2 H3 H5 J4" aw="D3 E2 E3 E4 F3 F4 F6 G3 G4 H4 H6"
Correct Answer

Black should atari with 1. Connecting with 2 doesn’t help White at all. Black 3 will capture nine stones.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia23) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=H5F5 ab="C3 D2 D4 E1 E5 F2 G2 H3 H5 J4" aw="D3 E2 E3 E4 F3 F4 F5 F6 G3 H4 H6"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White can connect to his stone on the outside with 2 and escape.

::h2
Problem 191

::dia(#ch9_1_dia24) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=G4K10E5K10G3 ab="E5 E6 E7 F5 G4 G6 H6 J6 K10" aw="F4 F6 F7 G3 G5 H4 H5 J5 K10"
Problem 191
Black to play

Two black stones are in atari. Which one should Black save?

::h3
Answer 191

::dia(#ch9_1_dia25) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=G6E7G5 ab="E7 E8 E9 F7 G6 G8 H8 J8" aw="F6 F8 F9 G5 G7 H6 H7 J7"
Correct Answer

Black has no choice but to connect with 1. After White captures with 2, Black’s territory at the top is intact.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia26) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=F7G5E7 ab="E8 E9 F7 G5 G6 G8 H8 J8" aw="E7 F6 F8 F9 G7 H6 H7 J7"
Wrong Answer

If Black saves this stone by playing 1, White captures with 2, and Black’s stones are scattered without a base. This is a disaster for Black.

::h2
Problem 192

::dia(#ch9_1_dia27) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=D15E15F15M19F13M19E14 ab="C13 C14 D13 D15 E13 E15 F12 F13 F15 G13 G14 H15 J12 J15 K12 K13 K14 M19" aw="C15 C16 D14 D16 E14 E16 F14 F16 G12 G15 G16 H12 H13 H14 J13 M19"
Problem 192
Black to play

A group of two and a group of three black stones are in atari. Which group should Black save?

::h3
Answer 192

::dia(#ch9_1_dia28) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=D15E15F15F13E14 ab="C13 C14 D13 D15 E13 E15 F12 F13 F15 G13 G14 H15 J12 J15 K12 K13 K14" aw="C15 C16 D14 D16 E14 E16 F14 F16 G12 G15 G16 H12 H13 H14 J13"
Correct Answer

Black should play 1, saving two stones and sacrificing three. In this way, he kills the five white stones on the right.

::dia(#ch9_1_dia29) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=D14G14G13E14F13 ab="C13 C14 D13 D15 E13 E14 E15 F12 F15 G13 G14 H15 J12 J15 K12 K13 K14" aw="C15 C16 D14 D16 E16 F13 F14 F16 G12 G15 G16 H12 H13 H14 J13"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White captures two stones with 2 and his five stones on the right are now connected to the ones above.


::chapter(#ch9_2)

::h3
Capturing Races

::h2
Problem 193

::dia(#ch9_2_dia0) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19E19 ab="D18 E17 E19 F17 G18 H18 L19" aw="E18 F18 G17 H17 J18"
Problem 193
Black to play

How can Black capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 193

::dia(#ch9_2_dia1) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=E19 ab="D18 E17 E19 F17 G18 H18" aw="E18 F18 G17 H17 J18"
Correct Answer

If Black ataries with 1, he will capture two white stones.

::dia(#ch9_2_dia2) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=H19 ab="D18 E17 F17 G18 H18" aw="E18 F18 G17 H17 H19 J18"
If White Plays First

If it were White’s turn to play, he would atari with 1 and capture two black stones.

::h2
Problem 194

::dia(#ch9_2_dia3) sz=13 vw=A7N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13H7J9 ab="E7 E8 E9 F9 G10 H10 H7 H8 J10 J8 J9 K9 N13" aw="C9 D10 D8 E10 F10 F8 G7 G8 G9 H9"
Problem 194
Black to play

How can Black capture five white stones?

(There are two correct answers.)

::h3
Answer 194

::dia(#ch9_2_dia4) sz=13 vw=A7N13 base=none at=1 mv=H7 ab="E7 E8 E9 F9 G10 H10 H7 H8 J10 J8 K9" aw="C9 D10 D8 E10 F10 F8 G7 G8 G9 H9"
