Either Black 1 or Black A will capture five white stones.

::dia(#ch9_2_dia5) sz=13 vw=A7N13 base=none at=1 mv=F7D7 ab="E7 E8 E9 F7 F9 G10 H10 H8 J10 J8 K9" aw="C9 D10 D7 D8 E10 F10 F8 G7 G8 G9 H9"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 fails. White answers with 2, putting five black stones into atari.

::h2
Problem 195

::dia(#ch9_2_dia6) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10E7 ab="C6 C7 D4 D5 E6 E7 F6 G6 K10" aw="D6 D7 E5 F5 G5 G7 H6"
Problem 195
Black to play

How can Black capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 195

::dia(#ch9_2_dia7) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=E9 ab="C8 C9 D6 D7 E8 E9 F8 G8" aw="D8 D9 E7 F7 G7 G9 H8"
Correct Answer

Black 1 captures two white stones.

::dia(#ch9_2_dia8) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=D10E9 ab="C8 C9 D10 D6 D7 E8 F8 G8" aw="D8 D9 E7 E9 F7 G7 G9 H8"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries from below with 1, White 2 will capture three black stones.

::h2
Problem 196

::dia(#ch9_2_dia9) sz=13 vw=A7M13 base=none at=1 mv=M13G7 ab="E10 E7 E8 E9 F11 G10 G7 G9 H8 H9 J8 M13" aw="F10 F7 F8 F9 G11 H10 H11 J7 J9 K10 K8"
Problem 196
Black to play

How can Black capture four white stones?

(There are two correct answers.)

::h3
Answer 196

::dia(#ch9_2_dia10) sz=13 vw=A7M13 base=none at=1 mv=G7 ab="E10 E7 E8 E9 F11 G10 G7 G9 H8 H9 J8" aw="F10 F7 F8 F9 G11 H10 H11 J7 J9 K10 K8"
Correct Answer

Putting the four white stones into atari with Black 1 or A is the right move. These stones will be captured on the next move.

::dia(#ch9_2_dia11) sz=13 vw=A7M13 base=none at=1 mv=H7K7 ab="E10 E7 E8 E9 F11 G10 G9 H7 H8 H9 J8" aw="F10 F7 F8 F9 G11 H10 H11 J7 J9 K10 K7 K8"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries with 1, he fails. White connects with 2 and the position becomes a seki.


::chapter(#ch9_3)

::h3
Nets

::h2
Problem 197

::dia(#ch9_3_dia0) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19E15 ab="E15 E17 F17 G15 G16 J15 L19" aw="C14 C15 C16 C17 F16 G17 G18 J17"
Problem 197
Black to play

