Correct Answer

Black will capture one stone in a net when he plays 1. This stone cannot escape and will be captured.

::dia(#ch9_3_dia2) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=E16F15 ab="E16 E17 F17 G15 G16 J15" aw="C14 C15 C16 C17 F15 F16 G17 G18 J17"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 fails. White plays 2 and he cannot be captured.

::h2
Problem 198

::dia(#ch9_3_dia3) sz=19 vw=A11M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19H16 ab="E15 E16 F14 F16 G14 H14 H16 M19" aw="C14 D15 E13 E14 F15 G15 K14 K15 K16"
Problem 198
Black to play

How can Black capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 198

::dia(#ch9_3_dia4) sz=19 vw=A11M19 base=none at=1 mv=H16 ab="E15 E16 F14 F16 G14 H14 H16" aw="C14 D15 E13 E14 F15 G15 K14 K15 K16"
Correct Answer

Black 1 captures two stones in a net. These stones cannot escape and will be captured.

::dia(#ch9_3_dia5) sz=19 vw=A11M19 base=none at=1 mv=G16H15 ab="E15 E16 F14 F16 G14 G16 H14" aw="C14 D15 E13 E14 F15 G15 H15 K14 K15 K16"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 fails. White plays 2 and his stones cannot be captured.

::h2
