Problem 200

::dia(#ch9_3_dia9) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19G13 ab="C12 C13 C14 C15 C16 D12 E13 E14 G13 L19" aw="D13 D14 D15 D17 E12 E15 E17 F12 G16 H16 J13 J14 J15"
Problem 200
Black to play

How can Black capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 200

::dia(#ch9_3_dia10) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=G13 ab="C12 C13 C14 C15 C16 D12 E13 E14 G13" aw="D13 D14 D15 D17 E12 E15 E17 F12 G16 H16 J13 J14 J15"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is an example of a net played on the edge of the board. The two white stones cannot escape.

::dia(#ch9_3_dia11) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=F13G12G13H12 ab="C12 C13 C14 C15 C16 D12 E13 E14 F13 G13" aw="D13 D14 D15 D17 E12 E15 E17 F12 G12 G16 H12 H16 J13 J14 J15"
