Problem 202
Black to play

Capture three white stones with a snapback.

::h3
Answer 202

::dia(#ch9_4_dia4) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=D5 ab="C6 D5 D7 E4 E7 F5 F7 G6" aw="C5 D4 D6 E6 F6 G4 G5"
Correct Answer

Black can capture three white stones with 1. White cannot capture because of a snapback.

::dia(#ch9_4_dia5) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=E5D5 ab="C6 D7 E4 E5 E7 F5 F7 G6" aw="C5 D4 D5 D6 E6 F6 G4 G5"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 fails. White connects with 2 and his stones are safe.

::h2
Problem 203

::dia(#ch9_4_dia6) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10E3 ab="C4 D4 E3 E5 F2 F5 G2 G4 H3 H4 K10" aw="C3 D3 D5 D6 E2 E4 F4 G3 G5 G6"
Problem 203
Black to play

Three white stones can be captured with a snapback.

::h3
Answer 203

::dia(#ch9_4_dia7) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=E5 ab="C6 D6 E5 E7 F4 F7 G4 G6 H5 H6" aw="C5 D5 D7 D8 E4 E6 F6 G5 G7 G8"
Correct Answer

Black 1 sets up a snapback and catches three white stones.

::dia(#ch9_4_dia8) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=G5F5E5 ab="C6 D6 E7 F4 F5 F7 G4 G6 H5 H6" aw="C5 D5 D7 D8 E4 E5 E6 F6 G5 G7 G8"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 captures one stone, but it lets White save his other two by connecting at 2. Black has failed.

::h2
Problem 204

::dia(#ch9_4_dia9) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19D12 ab="C14 D12 D13 D15 E16 F13 F15 G12 G14 G15 M19" aw="D14 E12 E13 E14 E15 F14 G13 H13 H14 J13"
Problem 204
Black to play

How can Black capture six white stones with a snapback?

::h3
Answer 204

::dia(#ch9_4_dia10) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 mv=D12 ab="C14 D12 D13 D15 E16 F13 F15 G12 G14 G15" aw="D14 E12 E13 E14 E15 F14 G13 H13 H14 J13"
Correct Answer

Black 1 sets up a snapback and six white stones can now be captured.

::dia(#ch9_4_dia11) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 mv=F13G12F12H12 ab="C14 D13 D15 E16 F12 F13 F15 G12 G14 G15" aw="D14 E12 E13 E14 E15 F14 G13 H12 H13 H14 J13"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 fails. White 2 captures three black stones and all of White’s stones are safe.


::chapter(#ch9_5)

::h3
Oiotoshi

::h2
Problem 205

::dia(#ch9_5_dia0) sz=13 vw=A7N13 base=none at=1 mv=N13D13 ab="D12 D13 E11 F11 F12 G11 H11 J10 J12 N13" aw="C11 D11 E12 E13 F13 G12 H12 H13 J11 K11 K12"
Problem 205
Black to play

Capture three white stones using the connect-and-capture technique.

::h3
Answer 205

::dia(#ch9_5_dia1) sz=13 vw=A7N13 base=none at=1 mv=D13 ab="D12 D13 E11 F11 F12 G11 H11 J10 J12" aw="C11 D11 E12 E13 F13 G12 H12 H13 J11 K11 K12"
Correct Answer

Black plays 1. If White connects his three stones that are in atari, they will still be in atari and Black will capture six stones.

::dia(#ch9_5_dia2) sz=13 vw=A7N13 base=none at=1 mv=J12J13K13 ab="D12 E11 F11 F12 G11 H11 J10 J12 J13" aw="C11 D11 E12 E13 F13 G12 H12 H13 J11 K11 K12 K13"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White captures two stones with 2 and all of White’s stones are safe.

::h2
Problem 206

::dia(#ch9_5_dia3) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10E5 ab="D2 D3 D4 D6 E1 E5 F1 F6 G1 G2 G4 G5 K10" aw="D1 E2 E3 E4 F2 F4 F5 G3 H1 H2 H4"
Problem 206
Black to play

Capture six white stones using the connect-and-capture technique.

::h3
Answer 206

::dia(#ch9_5_dia4) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=E7 ab="D4 D5 D6 D8 E3 E7 F3 F8 G3 G4 G6 G7" aw="D2 D3 E4 E5 E6 F4 F6 F7 G5 H3 H4 H6"
Correct Answer

Black 1 puts six white stones into atari. If White connects, his stones will still be in atari, so Black will capture seven stones.

::dia(#ch9_5_dia5) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=H7H5E7F5 ab="D4 D5 D6 D8 E3 E7 F3 F8 G3 G4 G6 G7 H7" aw="D2 D3 E4 E5 E6 F4 F5 F6 F7 G5 H3 H4 H5 H6"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 lets White off the hook. White connects with 2. If Black now ataries with 3, White connects with 4 and all his stones are safe.

::h2
Problem 207

::dia(#ch9_5_dia6) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19G19L19F19D19 ab="D18 D19 E18 F17 G17 G19 H17 H18 L19" aw="C17 D17 E17 E19 F18 F19 G18 H19 J17 J18 L19"
Problem 207
Black to play

Capture three white stones with the connect-and-capture technique.

::h3
Answer 207

::dia(#ch9_5_dia7) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=G19F19D19 ab="D18 D19 E18 F17 G17 G19 H17 H18" aw="C17 D17 E17 E19 F18 F19 G18 H19 J17 J18"
Correct Answer

Black sacrifices a stone with 1, then plays 3. White can’t connect, so he has lost four stones.

::dia(#ch9_5_dia8) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=D19G19 ab="D18 D19 E18 F17 G17 H17 H18" aw="C17 D17 E17 E19 F18 G18 G19 H19 J17 J18"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1 first, he fails. White connects with 2 and his stones are safe.

::h2
Problem 208

::dia(#ch9_5_dia9) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10J1 ab="F2 G1 G2 H2 J1 J3 K1 K10" aw="D1 E2 E3 F1 F4 G1 H1 H4 J1 J4"
Problem 208
Black to play

Capture three white stones with the connect-and-capture technique.

::h3
Answer 208

::dia(#ch9_5_dia10) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=J1 ab="F4 G2 G3 G4 H4 J1 J3 J5 K2" aw="D3 E4 E5 F2 F3 F6 G1 H2 H3 H6 J2 J6"
Correct Answer

Black 1 will capture the three white stones in the corner.

::dia(#ch9_5_dia11) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=H1J1 ab="F4 G2 G3 G4 H1 H4 J3 J5 K2" aw="D3 E4 E5 F2 F3 F6 G1 H2 H3 H6 J1 J2 J6"
Wrong Answer

In this case, sacrificing a stone with 1 will fail. After White 2, Black has no follow-up move to capture White.


::chapter(#ch9_6)

::h3
Brilliant Moves and Bad Moves

::h2
Problem 209

::dia(#ch9_6_dia0) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 mv=F1E1Q16F1K17 ab="C15 C3 D17 D4 E1 E3 E4 F1 F2 G1 G2 G4 K3" aw="B4 C2 C4 C6 D1 D2 D3 E2 F1 K17 Q16 Q3 R5"
Problem 209 – Which side has profited?
(Black 3 is played to the right of Black 1)

Black has captured and resolved the ko with 1 and 3, while White has occupied an empty corner and extended along the upper side with 2 and 4. Which side has profited more in this sequence?

::h3
Answer 209

::dia(#ch9_6_dia1) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 ab="C15 C3 D17 D4 E1 E3 E4 F1 F2 G1 G2 G4 K3" aw="B4 C2 C4 C6 D1 D2 D3 E2 K17 Q16 Q3 R5"
Correct Answer

White has profited more with the sequence in the problem Diagram. If you compare the diagram above with the one below, the difference will be clear.

::dia(#ch9_6_dia2) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 mv=Q16 ab="C15 C3 D17 D4 E3 E4 F2 G1 G2 G4 K3 Q16" aw="B4 C2 C4 C6 D1 D2 D3 E2 F1 Q3 R5"
For Reference

Occupying an empty corner with Black 1 is the most profitable move for Black. Black is better by about 30 points than the diagram above.

::h2
Problem 210

::dia(#ch9_6_dia3) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=H19 ab="E17 E18 F17 F19 G17 G18 G19 H17 H19 J17 J18 J19" aw="D17 D18 D19 E16 E19 F16 G16 H16 H18 J16 K17 K18 K19"
Problem 210 – Good or bad?

Black has captured a stone with 1. Is this a good or a bad move?

::h3
Answer 210

::dia(#ch9_6_dia4) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=H19 ab="E17 E18 F17 F19 G17 G18 G19 H17 H19 J17 J18 J19" aw="D17 D18 D19 E16 E19 F16 G16 H16 H18 J16 K17 K18 K19"
Black 1 is Bad

Black 1 is a bad move because it is completely unnecessary.

::dia(#ch9_6_dia5) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 ab="E17 E18 F17 F19 G17 G18 G19 H17 J17 J18 J19" aw="D17 D18 D19 E16 E19 F16 G16 H16 H18 J16 K17 K18 K19"
For Reference

Black should leave the situation as it is. By playing at 1 he loses one point of territory.

::h2
Problem 211

::dia(#ch9_6_dia6) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 mv=G14 ab="E13 E14 F13 F15 G14 G15 H14 K14" aw="D13 D14 E15 E16 F14"
Problem 211 – Good or bad?

Black has captured a stone with 1. Is this a good or a bad move?

::h3
Answer 211

::dia(#ch9_6_dia7) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 mv=G14 ab="E13 E14 F13 F15 G14 G15 H14 K14" aw="D13 D14 E15 E16 F14"
Black 1 is Bad

Black 1 is a bad move. It is unnecessary for Black to play this move at this time.

::dia(#ch9_6_dia8) sz=19 vw=A12M19 base=none at=1 ab="E13 E14 F13 F15 G15 H14 K14" aw="D13 D14 E15 E16 F14"
For Reference

Even if White plays at A he cannot escape, so there is no need to play a move here.


::chapter(#ch9_7)

::h3
Seki

::h2
Problem 212

::dia(#ch9_7_dia0) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10G8 ab="D6 D7 D8 E6 F5 G5 G6 G7 G8 K10" aw="C5 C6 C7 C8 D5 E5 F6 F7 F8"
Problem 212
Black to play

Make a seki between the four black stones on the left and the three white stones on the right.

::h3
Answer 212

::dia(#ch9_7_dia1) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=G10 ab="D10 D8 D9 E8 F7 G10 G7 G8 G9" aw="C10 C7 C8 C9 D7 E7 F10 F8 F9"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, a seki results between the four black and the three white stones.

::dia(#ch9_7_dia2) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=D10D9D8E8E9G10E10 ab="D10 D8 D9 E8 F7 G10 G7 G8 G9" aw="C10 C7 C8 C9 D7 E10 E7 E9 F10 F8 F9"
If White Plays First

If it were White’s turn, he could capture the four black stones with 1 and 3.

::h2
Problem 213

::dia(#ch9_7_dia3) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19G12 ab="C14 D12 D13 E14 E15 E16 F16 G12 G15 H12 H13 H14 H15 L19" aw="E12 E13 F13 F14 F15 G13 G16 H16 J12 J13 J14 J15"
Problem 213
Black to play

How can Black make a seki?

::h3
Answer 213

::dia(#ch9_7_dia4) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=G12 ab="C14 D12 D13 E14 E15 E16 F16 G12 G15 H12 H13 H14 H15" aw="E12 E13 F13 F14 F15 G13 G16 H16 J12 J13 J14 J15"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, a seki results between the six white stones and the six black stones.

::dia(#ch9_7_dia5) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=J16G12 ab="C14 D12 D13 E14 E15 E16 F16 G15 H12 H13 H14 H15 J16" aw="E12 E13 F13 F14 F15 G12 G13 G16 H16 J12 J13 J14 J15"
Wrong Answer

If Black makes any other move, such as 1, White plays 2 and captures five black stones.

::h2
Problem 214

::dia(#ch9_7_dia6) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19G19 ab="D15 D16 D17 D18 D19 E15 F15 G15 G18 G19 H16 H17 H18 J18 J19 M19" aw="E16 E17 E18 E19 F16 F18 G16 G17 H15 J15 J16 J17 K18 K19"
Problem 214
Black to play

How can Black make a seki?

::h3
Answer 214

::dia(#ch9_7_dia7) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=G19 ab="D15 D16 D17 D18 D19 E15 F15 G15 G18 G19 H16 H17 H18 J18 J19" aw="E16 E17 E18 E19 F16 F18 G16 G17 H15 J15 J16 J17 K18 K19"
Correct Answer

Black 1 creates a seki between the eight white stones on the left and seven black stones on the right.

::dia(#ch9_7_dia8) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 ab="D15 D16 D17 D18 D19 E15 F15 G15 G18 G19 H16 H17 H18 J18 J19" aw="E16 E17 E18 E19 F16 F18 G16 G17 H15 J15 J16 J17 K18 K19"
For Reference

In this seki, both sides have an eye, but these eyes are not counted as territory.

::h2
Problem 215

::dia(#ch9_7_dia9) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19D16 ab="C14 C15 C16 D13 D16 D17 E13 E16 F13 F16 G13 G14 G16 H13 H15 H16 M19" aw="C12 C13 D12 D14 D15 E12 E15 F12 F15 G12 G15 H12 H14 J13 J14"
Problem 215
Black to play

How can Black make a seki?

::h3
Answer 215

::dia(#ch9_7_dia10) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=D16 ab="C14 C15 C16 D13 D16 D17 E13 E16 F13 F16 G13 G14 G16 H13 H15 H16" aw="C12 C13 D12 D14 D15 E12 E15 F12 F15 G12 G15 H12 H14 J13 J14"
Correct Answer

Black 1 results in a seki between the five white stones and the six black stones.

::dia(#ch9_7_dia11) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=E14 ab="C14 C15 C16 D13 D17 E13 E14 E16 F13 F16 G13 G14 G16 H13 H15 H16" aw="C12 C13 D12 D14 D15 E12 E15 F12 F15 G12 G15 H12 H14 J13 J14"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 fails. The black stones are dead as they stand; White can capture them any time he wants.


::chapter(#ch9_8)

::h3
Connecting and Separating Stones

::h2
Problem 216

::dia(#ch9_8_dia0) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10F7 ab="D6 E6 F7 G6 H6 K10" aw="F3 F5 F6"
Problem 216
Black to play

How can Black link up his stones on the left to the ones on the right?

::h3
Answer 216

::dia(#ch9_8_dia1) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=F9 ab="D8 E8 F9 G8 H8" aw="F5 F7 F8"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, the black stones on the left and right are linked up and White cannot separate them.

::dia(#ch9_8_dia2) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=F9 ab="D8 E8 G8 H8" aw="F5 F7 F8 F9"
If White Plays First

If it were White ’s turn, he would play 1 and the black stones would be split into two groups.

::h2
Problem 217

::dia(#ch9_8_dia3) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10G1 ab="E1 F2 G1 H2 J2 K10" aw="G2 G3 G5 J4"
Problem 217
Black to play

How can Black link up his stones on the left to the two on the right?

::h3
Answer 217

::dia(#ch9_8_dia4) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=G3 ab="E3 F4 G3 H4 J4" aw="G4 G5 G7 J6"
Correct Answer

By playing 1, Black links up his stones on the left and right.

::dia(#ch9_8_dia5) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=G3 ab="E3 F4 H4 J4" aw="G3 G4 G5 G7 J6"
If White Plays First

If it were White’s turn, he would play 1 and the black stones would be split into two groups.

::h2
Problem 218

::dia(#ch9_8_dia6) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19F16 ab="C16 D17 E16 F16 G17 H16 H17 L19" aw="E17 F14 F17 G15 G16"
Problem 218
Black to play

How can Black separate White into two groups?

::h3
Answer 218

::dia(#ch9_8_dia7) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=F16 ab="C16 D17 E16 F16 G17 H16 H17" aw="E17 F14 F17 G15 G16"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, the two white stones above are separated from the ones below. The two white stones above will be captured.

::dia(#ch9_8_dia8) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=F16 ab="C16 D17 E16 G17 H16 H17" aw="E17 F14 F16 F17 G15 G16"
If White Plays First

If it were White’s turn, he would connect with 1. All of White’s stones are now linked up.

::h2
Problem 219

::dia(#ch9_8_dia9) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19F15 ab="D14 D15 F15 G15 J15 L19" aw="D17 F14 F16"
Problem 219
Black to play

Where should Black play?

::h3
Answer 219

::dia(#ch9_8_dia10) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=F15 ab="D14 D15 F15 G15 J15" aw="D17 F14 F16"
Correct Answer

By playing at 1, the white stone below is cut off from the two above. It will eventually be captured.

::dia(#ch9_8_dia11) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=F15 ab="D14 D15 G15 J15" aw="D17 F14 F15 F16"
If White Plays First

If it were White’s turn, he would connect with 1. His stones are now very strong.

::h2
Problem 220

::dia(#ch9_8_dia12) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10C6 ab="C5 C6 D5 E6 F6 G5 K10" aw="C4 D4 D6 E4 E5"
Problem 220
Black to play

How should Black atari the lone white stone?

::h3
Answer 220

::dia(#ch9_8_dia13) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=C8 ab="C7 C8 D7 E8 F8 G7" aw="C6 D6 D8 E6 E7"
Correct Answer

If Black ataries with 1, the white stone cannot avoid capture and Black’s stones will be linked up into one group.

::dia(#ch9_8_dia14) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=D9C8B7B8 ab="B7 C7 D7 D9 E8 F8 G7" aw="B8 C6 C8 D6 D8 E6 E7"
Wrong Answer

If Black ataries with 1, after the sequence to White 4, the black stones cannot avoid capture.

::h2
Problem 221

::dia(#ch9_8_dia15) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19E16 ab="D15 E14 E16 F12 F13 F14 F17 G15 G17 H15 L19" aw="C15 C16 D12 D13 D14 D17 E17 F15 F16 G14 H12 H14 J14"
Problem 221
Black to play

How can Black cut off and capture two white stones?

::h3
Answer 221

::dia(#ch9_8_dia16) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=E16 ab="D15 E14 E16 F12 F13 F14 F17 G15 G17 H15" aw="C15 C16 D12 D13 D14 D17 E17 F15 F16 G14 H12 H14 J14"
Correct Answer

Black 1 captures two white stones. Black’s stones above and below are now linked up.

::dia(#ch9_8_dia17) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=E15E16 ab="D15 E14 E15 F12 F13 F14 F17 G15 G17 H15" aw="C15 C16 D12 D13 D14 D17 E16 E17 F15 F16 G14 H12 H14 J14"
Wrong Answer

If Black connects with 1, he fails. White would connect with 2 and the six black stones below are cut off from its allies above. They will eventually be captured.


::chapter(#ch9_9)

::h3
Living and Dead Groups

::h2
Problem 222

::dia(#ch9_9_dia0) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10J8 ab="G7 H6 H7 J6 J8 K10 K7" aw="E6 F7 G5 G6 H5 J5 K5 K6"
Problem 222
Black to play

How can Black secure life for his stones?

::h3
Answer 222

::dia(#ch9_9_dia1) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=J10 ab="G9 H8 H9 J10 J8 K9" aw="E8 F9 G7 G8 H7 J7 K7 K8"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, he has two eyes, so his stones are alive.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia2) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=G10J10 ab="G10 G9 H8 H9 J8 K9" aw="E8 F9 G7 G8 H7 J10 J7 K7 K8"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White 2 reduces the black group to one eye and it will eventually be captured.

::h2
Problem 223

::dia(#ch9_9_dia3) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10B2 ab="A3 B2 B4 C4 D3 D4 K10" aw="A4 A5 B5 C5 D5 E3 E4 G3"
Problem 223
Black to play

How can Black secure life for his stones?

::h3
Answer 223

::dia(#ch9_9_dia4) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=B4 ab="A5 B4 B6 C6 D5 D6" aw="A6 A7 B7 C7 D7 E5 E6 G5"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, his group gets two eyes and cannot be killed.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia5) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=B5C4 ab="A5 B5 B6 C6 D5 D6" aw="A6 A7 B7 C4 C7 D7 E5 E6 G5"
Wrong Answer

In response to Black 1, White plays 2. Black’s group can no longer make two eyes, so it will die.

::h2
Problem 224

::dia(#ch9_9_dia6) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10J8 ab="E7 E8 F6 F8 G5 G6 G7 H8 J7 J8 K10 K7" aw="C6 D7 D8 E5 E6 F5 G4 H4 H5 H6 H7 J6"
Problem 224
Black to play

How can Black secure life for his stones?

::h3
Answer 224

::dia(#ch9_9_dia7) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=J10 ab="E10 E9 F10 F8 G7 G8 G9 H10 J10 J9 K9" aw="C8 D10 D9 E7 E8 F7 G6 H6 H7 H8 H9 J8"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, his group has two eyes, so it is alive.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia8) sz=19 vw=A4K10 base=none at=1 mv=J10K10 ab="E10 E9 F10 F8 G7 G8 G9 H10 J9 K10 K9" aw="C8 D10 D9 E7 E8 F7 G6 H6 H7 H8 H9 J10 J8"
If White Plays First

If it were White’s turn, he would sacrifice a stone at 1. After Black captures with 2, his two eyes on the edge are false. He has only one real eye, so he dies.

::h2
Problem 225

::dia(#ch9_9_dia9) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19G16M19J15H15 ab="F12 F13 F15 F16 G12 G14 G16 H12 H13 H14 H15 H16 J14 M19" aw="E12 E13 E14 E15 E16 F11 F14 F17 G11 G17 H11 H17 J12 J15 J17 K13 K14 K15 K16 M19"
Problem 225
Black to play

How can Black secure life for his stones?

::h3
Answer 225

::dia(#ch9_9_dia10) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=G16J15H15 ab="F12 F13 F15 F16 G12 G14 G16 H12 H13 H14 H15 H16 J14" aw="E12 E13 E14 E15 E16 F11 F14 F17 G11 G17 H11 H17 J12 J15 J17 K13 K14 K15 K16"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, he can play 3 in response to White’s only threat at 2. Black now has two eyes, so he is alive.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia11) sz=19 vw=A10M19 base=none at=1 mv=J15G16G15J16 ab="F12 F13 F15 F16 G12 G14 G15 H12 H13 H14 H16 J14 J15" aw="E12 E13 E14 E15 E16 F11 F14 F17 G11 G16 G17 H11 H17 J12 J16 J17 K13 K14 K15 K16"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White 2 and 4 reduce the eye at the top to a false one, so Black is dead.

::h2
Problem 226

::dia(#ch9_9_dia12) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10F8K10E8G8 ab="D5 D6 D7 E3 E4 F3 F8 G3 G8 H4 H5 H6 H7 K10" aw="E5 E6 E7 E8 F4 F6 G4 G5 G6 G7 K10"
Problem 226
Black to play

How can Black kill the white group?

::h3
Answer 226

::dia(#ch9_9_dia13) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=F10E10G10 ab="D7 D8 D9 E5 E6 F10 F5 G10 G5 H6 H7 H8 H9" aw="E10 E7 E8 E9 F6 F8 G6 G7 G8 G9"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, White’s group cannot make two eyes, so it is dead. If White plays 2 at 3, Black will play at 2 with the same result.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia14) sz=19 vw=A3K10 base=none at=1 mv=G10F10 ab="D7 D8 D9 E5 E6 F5 G10 G5 H6 H7 H8 H9" aw="E7 E8 E9 F10 F6 F8 G6 G7 G8 G9"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, he fails. White’s group gets two perfect eyes when he plays at 2, so it is alive.

::h2
Problem 227

::dia(#ch9_9_dia15) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=H13M19G15M19J13G16 ab="C15 D14 E15 E16 F17 G15 G16 G17 H13 H16 J14 J16 K14 K15 M19" aw="E13 E14 F14 F15 F16 G13 H14 H15 J13 J15 M19"
Problem 227
Black to play

How can Black kill the white group?

::h3
Answer 227

::dia(#ch9_9_dia16) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=H13G15J13G16 ab="C15 D14 E15 E16 F17 G15 G16 G17 H13 H16 J14 J16 K14 K15" aw="E13 E14 F14 F15 F16 G13 H14 H15 J13 J15"
Correct Answer

Black 1 and 3 kill White’s group. Even though White has captured a black stone, he has only made a false eye.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia17) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=J13G16 ab="C15 D14 E15 E16 F17 G17 H13 H16 J13 J14 J16 K14 K15" aw="E13 E14 F14 F15 F16 G13 G16 H14 H15 J15"
Wrong Answer

If Black connects with 1, White gets two eyes when he plays at 2. His group is absolutely alive.

::h2
Problem 228

::dia(#ch9_9_dia18) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19F18 ab="D16 D17 D18 D19 E16 F15 G15 H15 H17 H19 J17 J19 K15 K18 K19" aw="E17 E18 E19 F16 F18 G16 G17 G19 H18 J18 M19"
Problem 228
White to play

How can White secure life for his stones?

::h3
Answer 228

::dia(#ch9_9_dia19) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=F18 ab="D16 D17 D18 D19 E16 F15 G15 H15 H17 H19 J17 J19 K15 K18 K19" aw="E17 E18 E19 F16 F18 G16 G17 G19 H18 J18"
Correct Answer

White 1 makes two eyes. Even if Black captures two stones on the next move, White will recapture and he still has two eyes.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia20) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=G18F18 ab="D16 D17 D18 D19 E16 F15 F18 G15 H15 H17 H19 J17 J19 K15 K18 K19" aw="E17 E18 E19 F16 G16 G17 G18 G19 H18 J18"
Wrong Answer

If White connnects with 1, his group dies. Black plays on the vital point of 2 and White cannot make two eyes.

::h2
Problem 229

::dia(#ch9_9_dia21) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19G13M19J13E13J13G13 ab="C15 D14 E15 E16 F16 G13 G16 H15 J13 J15 K14 K15 M19" aw="E13 E14 F14 F15 G13 G15 H14 J13 J14 M19"
Problem 229
White to play

How can White secure life for his stones?

::h3
Answer 229

::dia(#ch9_9_dia22) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=G13J13E13 ab="C15 D14 E15 E16 F16 G16 H15 J13 J15 K14 K15" aw="E13 E14 F14 F15 G13 G15 H14 J14"
Correct Answer

If White plays 1, his group is alive. If Black plays 2, White 3; if Black 2 at 3, White will play 3 at 2. Either way, White’s group gets two eyes.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia23) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=J13G13 ab="C15 D14 E15 E16 F16 G13 G16 H15 J15 K14 K15" aw="E14 F14 F15 G15 H14 J13 J14"
Wrong Answer

If White plays any other move, such as 1, Black will play on the vital point of 2 and White is dead.

::h2
Problem 230

::dia(#ch9_9_dia24) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19G18 ab="C17 C18 C19 D17 E17 F17 G16 G18 H16 J16 J17 J18 J19 L19" aw="D18 D19 E18 F18 F19 H17 H18 H19"
Problem 230
Black to play

How can Black kill the white group?

::h3
Answer 230

::dia(#ch9_9_dia25) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=G18 ab="C17 C18 C19 D17 E17 F17 G16 G18 H16 J16 J17 J18 J19" aw="D18 D19 E18 F18 F19 H17 H18 H19"
Correct Answer

If Black plays 1, White’s group cannot make two eyes, so it is dead.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia26) sz=19 vw=A13L19 base=none at=1 mv=G17G18 ab="C17 C18 C19 D17 E17 F17 G16 G17 H16 J16 J17 J18 J19" aw="D18 D19 E18 F18 F19 G18 H17 H18 H19"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, White makes two perfect eyes with 2 and his group is alive.

::h2
Problem 231

::dia(#ch9_9_dia27) sz=19 vw=A9L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19E15L19F15D16E15 ab="C15 C16 D12 D13 D14 D16 D17 E11 E15 E17 F11 F17 G11 G14 G17 H12 H13 H14 H15 H16 L19" aw="D15 E12 E13 E14 E15 E16 F12 F14 F15 F16 G12 G13 G15 G16 L19"
Problem 231
Black to play

How can Black kill the white group?

::h3
Answer 231

::dia(#ch9_9_dia28) sz=19 vw=A9L19 base=none at=1 mv=E15F15D16 ab="C15 C16 D12 D13 D14 D16 D17 E11 E15 E17 F11 F17 G11 G14 G17 H12 H13 H14 H15 H16" aw="D15 E12 E13 E14 E16 F12 F14 F15 F16 G12 G13 G15 G16"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the vital point. In response to White 2, Black plays 3. If White 2 at 3, Black 3 at 2. In either case, White is dead.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia29) sz=19 vw=A9L19 base=none at=1 mv=D16E15 ab="C15 C16 D12 D13 D14 D16 D17 E11 E17 F11 F17 G11 G14 G17 H12 H13 H14 H15 H16" aw="D15 E12 E13 E14 E15 E16 F12 F14 F16 G12 G13 G15 G16"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, he fails. White makes two perfect eyes by connecting at 2.

::h2
Problem 232

::dia(#ch9_9_dia30) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=M19F19 ab="C17 C18 C19 D17 E16 F16 G16 H17 J17 J18 J19" aw="D18 D19 E17 E18 F17 F19 G17 G18 H18 H19 M19"
Problem 232
White to play

How can White secure life for his group?

::h3
Answer 232

::dia(#ch9_9_dia31) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=F19 ab="C17 C18 C19 D17 E16 F16 G16 H17 J17 J18 J19" aw="D18 D19 E17 E18 F17 F19 G17 G18 H18 H19"
Correct Answer

White 1 is the vital point. White is absolutely alive.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia32) sz=19 vw=A13M19 base=none at=1 mv=F19 ab="C17 C18 C19 D17 E16 F16 F19 G16 H17 J17 J18 J19" aw="D18 D19 E17 E18 F17 G17 G18 H18 H19"
If Black Plays First

If it were Black’s turn, he would reduce White to one eye by playing 1. White’s group would eventually be captured.

::h2
Problem 233

::dia(#ch9_9_dia33) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19G12 ab="D12 D13 D14 D15 E12 E16 F11 F17 G11 G17 H16 H17 J12 J13 J14 J15" aw="E13 E14 E15 F12 F15 F16 G12 G13 G16 H13 H14 H15 L19"
Problem 233
White to play

How can White secure life for his stones?

::h3
Answer 233

::dia(#ch9_9_dia34) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=G12 ab="D12 D13 D14 D15 E12 E16 F11 F17 G11 G17 H16 H17 J12 J13 J14 J15" aw="E13 E14 E15 F12 F15 F16 G12 G13 G16 H13 H14 H15"
Correct Answer

White 1 is the vital point. White’s group is alive.

::dia(#ch9_9_dia35) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=G14 ab="D12 D13 D14 D15 E12 E16 F11 F17 G11 G17 H16 H17 J12 J13 J14 J15" aw="E13 E14 E15 F12 F15 F16 G13 G14 G16 H13 H14 H15"
For Reference

White could also live by playing 1, but he doesn’t make as much profit as he does in the correct answer.


::chapter(#ch9_10)

::h3
How to Play in the Opening

::h2
Problem 234

::dia(#ch9_10_dia0) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 mv=T19D4C3C4D3C5E3D5E4 ab="C3 C4 C5 D3 D4 D5 E3 E4 P17 R16 T19" aw="D16 R3"
Problem 234
Black to play

Where should Black make his next move?

(There is more than one correct answer.)

::h3
Answer 234

::dia(#ch9_10_dia1) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 mv=D4 ab="D4 P17 R16" aw="D16 R3"
Correct Answer

Black 1, or any of the points from A to D, would be correct. It is usually advantageous to take an empty corner in the opening.

::dia(#ch9_10_dia2) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 mv=R10D4 ab="P17 R10 R16" aw="D16 D4 R3"
Wrong Answer

Black 1 is, of course, a good point, but the empty corner is still better. After White plays 2, Black’s position is inferior.

::h2
Problem 235

::dia(#ch9_10_dia3) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 mv=T19K16K17J17J16 ab="F3 J16 J17 K16 K17 K4 Q10 Q16 Q4 T19" aw="C15 D17 D4 D6 D9"
Problem 235
Black to play

Where should Black make his next move?

(There is more than one correct answer.)

::h3
Answer 235

::dia(#ch9_10_dia4) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 mv=K16 ab="F3 K16 K4 Q10 Q16 Q4" aw="C15 D17 D4 D6 D9"
Correct Answer

In a position such as this, extending along the side is the usual way to play. Instead of Black 1, playing at A, B, or C would also be good.

::dia(#ch9_10_dia5) sz=19 vw=A1T19 base=none at=1 mv=K17 ab="F3 K4 Q10 Q16 Q4" aw="C15 D17 D4 D6 D9 K17"
For Reference

Playing on one of the points such as A, B, or C is not good. White takes a big strategic point on the side and has the advantage.


::chapter(#ch9_11)

::h3
Endgame

::h2
Problem 236

::dia(#ch9_11_dia0) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19F17 ab="C16 C17 C18 C19 D16 F15 F16 G15 H15 J14 K14 L14" aw="D17 D18 D19 E17 F17 G16 H16 J15 J17 K15 K17 L16 L19"
Problem 236
White to play

Where should White play to completely secure his territory?

::h3
Answer 236

::dia(#ch9_11_dia1) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=F17 ab="C16 C17 C18 C19 D16 F15 F16 G15 H15 J14 K14 L14" aw="D17 D18 D19 E17 F17 G16 H16 J15 J17 K15 K17 L16"
Correct Answer

White 1 seals off the territory at the top, securing 19 points of territory.

::dia(#ch9_11_dia2) sz=19 vw=A12L19 base=none at=1 mv=F17 ab="C16 C17 C18 C19 D16 F15 F16 F17 G15 H15 J14 K14 L14" aw="D17 D18 D19 E17 G16 H16 J15 J17 K15 K17 L16"
If Black Plays First

If it were Black’s turn, he would invade with 1 and devastate White’s territory at the top.

::h2
Problem 237

::dia(#ch9_11_dia3) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=L19F11 ab="A15 B14 B15 C15 D15 E16 F16 G12 G15 G16 H12 H13 H14 J10 J11" aw="A13 A14 B13 C14 D13 D14 E12 E14 E15 F11 F12 F15 G11 G13 G14 H10 H11 L19"
Problem 237
White to play

Where should White play to completely secure his territory?

::h3
Answer 237

::dia(#ch9_11_dia4) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=F11 ab="A15 B14 B15 C15 D15 E16 F16 G12 G15 G16 H12 H13 H14 J10 J11" aw="A13 A14 B13 C14 D13 D14 E12 E14 E15 F11 F12 F15 G11 G13 G14 H10 H11"
Correct Answer

White 1 defends the last defect in White’s territory at the bottom. This move secures 20 points of territory in the corner.

::dia(#ch9_11_dia5) sz=19 vw=A10L19 base=none at=1 mv=G11H11H10F11E11G10 ab="A15 B14 B15 C15 D15 E16 F11 F16 G10 G12 G15 G16 H12 H13 H14 J10 J11" aw="A13 A14 B13 C14 D13 D14 E11 E12 E14 E15 F12 F15 G11 G13 G14 H10 H11"
If Black Plays First

If it were Black’s turn to play, he would capture three stones with 1 and 3. This would make a big dent in White’s territory.

::h2
Problem 238

::dia(#ch9_11_dia6) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10E8 ab="D6 D7 E3 E4 E5 E6 E8 F3 F5 F6 G6 G7 G8 H3 H4 H5 H6 J3 J7 K10 K3" aw="C6 C7 C8 D2 D3 D4 D5 D8 E2 F2 G2 G3 H2 J2"
Problem 238 – Which is bigger?
Black to play

Which is the bigger point, A or B?

::h3
Answer 238

::dia(#ch9_11_dia7) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=E10 ab="D8 D9 E10 E5 E6 E7 E8 F5 F7 F8 G10 G8 G9 H5 H6 H7 H8 J5 J9 K5" aw="C10 C8 C9 D10 D4 D5 D6 D7 E4 F4 G4 G5 H4 J4"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the correct answer. This is where White would play if it were his turn.

::dia(#ch9_11_dia8) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=G6 ab="D8 D9 E5 E6 E7 E8 F5 F7 F8 G10 G6 G8 G9 H5 H6 H7 H8 J5 J9 K5" aw="C10 C8 C9 D10 D4 D5 D6 D7 E4 F4 G4 G5 H4 J4"
Wrong Answer

If Black plays 1, he gains one point less than the move in the correct answer.

::h2
Problem 239

::dia(#ch9_11_dia9) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=K10E1 ab="A1 A2 B1 B3 C1 C3 D1 D3 E1 E3 F1 F2 F3 K10" aw="A3 A4 B4 C4 D4 E1 E4 F1 F4 G1 G2 G3 G4"
Problem 239 – Which is bigger?
Black to play

Which is the bigger point, A or B?

::h3
Answer 239

::dia(#ch9_11_dia10) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=E3 ab="A2 A4 B3 B5 C2 C5 D1 D2 D5 E2 E3 E5 F2 F4 F5" aw="A5 A6 B6 C6 D6 E1 E6 F3 F6 G1 G2 G3 G4 G5 G6"
Correct Answer

Black 1 is the bigger point.

::dia(#ch9_11_dia11) sz=19 vw=A1K10 base=none at=1 mv=E1F1E3 ab="A2 A4 B3 B5 C2 C5 D1 D2 D5 E2 E5 F1 F2 F4 F5" aw="A5 A6 B6 C6 D6 E1 E3 E6 F3 F6 G1 G2 G3 G4 G5 G6"
Wrong Answer

If Black captures a stone with 1, White plays 2 and Black’s result is inferior to the correct answer by one point.


